BATCH CORRECTION XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

library(sva)
# pheno input
pheno <- rbind.data.frame(pData(exprset32323), pData(exprset8671))
pheno["group"] <- c(rep(c("Normal", "Cancer"), each = 17), rep(c("5aza_CancerCell",
    "cancerCell"), times = 5), rep(c("Normal", "Cancer"), each = 32))
pheno["batch"] <- c(rep(c("A", "B"), c(44, 64)))
# write.table(pheno, file = 'combat_edata_metadta.txt', quote = FALSE, sep =
# '\t', row.names = TRUE, col.names = TRUE)
# edata input
edata = cbind(exprs(exprset32323), exprs(exprset8671))
# create the full model matrix
mod = model.matrix(~as.factor(group), data = pheno)
# batch variable
batch <- pheno$batch
combat_edata <- ComBat(dat = edata, batch = batch, mod = mod)
dim(combat_edata)
## [1] 54675   108
# write.table(combat_edata, file = 'combat_edata.txt')
# convert affymatrix proble into gene symbols
library(biomaRt)

probes <- row.names(combat_edata)

mart <- biomaRt::useEnsembl(biomart = "ensembl", dataset = "hsapiens_gene_ensembl")

symbol_id_prob <- biomaRt::getBM(attributes = c("hgnc_symbol", "ensembl_gene_id",
    "affy_hg_u133_plus_2"), filters = "affy_hg_u133_plus_2", values = probes, mart = mart)

head(symbol_id_prob)

library(dplyr)
# symbol_id_prob <- as.data.frame(symbol_id_prob %>%
# group_by(affy_hg_u133_plus_2) %>% slice(1))

    distinct(affy_hg_u133_plus_2, .keep_all = TRUE)

# set row name
rownames(symbol_id_prob) <- symbol_id_prob$affy_hg_u133_plus_2

dim(symbol_id_prob)
## [1] 43024     3
# Combine gene annotations with raw data
combat_edata_symId = merge(symbol_id_prob, combat_edata, by = "row.names", all = TRUE)

# Write GCRMA-normalized, mapped data to file write.table(combat_edata_symId,
# file = 'combat_edata_symId.txt', quote = FALSE, sep = '\t', row.names =
# FALSE, col.names = TRUE)

read data

# combat_edata_symId <- read.delim('combat_edata_symId.txt')
library(dplyr)
# calculate median value for each gene
combat_edata_symMedian <- combat_edata_symId %>%
    group_by(hgnc_symbol) %>%
    summarise_at(vars(colnames(combat_edata_symId[, 5:112])), median)

# drop rows with hgnc_symbo = na
library(tidyr)
combat_edata_symMedian <- combat_edata_symMedian %>%
    drop_na(hgnc_symbol)

# use hgnc_symbl as row names
rownames(combat_edata_symMedian) <- combat_edata_symMedian$hgnc_symbol
combat_edata_symMedian <- combat_edata_symMedian[, 2:109]

## get the name of the top 10 measurements (genes) that contribute most to pc1.

gene_score_ranked <- sort(gene_scores, decreasing = TRUE)
top_10_genes <- names(gene_score_ranked[1:10])

top_10_genes  ## show the names of the top 10 genes

library(pheatmap)
# hierarchical clustering in the same manner as performed by pheatmap to obtain
# gene clusters
library(dendextend)
hclust_gene <- hclust(dist(combat_edata_symMedian), method = "complete")

as.dendrogram(hclust_gene) %>%
    plot(horiz = TRUE)

# cut tree for k = 3
gene_row <- cutree(tree = as.dendrogram(hclust_gene), k = 3)
